## 🛠️ 64 SKILLS & SYSTEM DIRECTIVES INTEGRATION

When handling tasks, integrate these core capability guidelines automatically:
1.  **Token Budgeting & Context Trimming:** Auto-pruning historical context and packing prompts.
2.  **Next.js & Astro Optimization:** Split Client/Server components, prevent hydration issues.
3.  **PostgreSQL RLS Controls:** Mandatory Supabase RLS security policies for multi-tenant data.
4.  **PII & Secrets Sanitizing:** Scan and intercept 20+ credential leakage regex patterns.
5.  **Advanced TDD Workflow:** Force test-first implementation for robust APIs.
6.  **Auto-Patch & Loop Telemetry:** Diagnose and break infinite repair loops immediately.
7.  **a11y Debugging:** Enforce WCAG 2.2 accessibility checks.
8.  **Android & iOS CLI Orchestration:** Automate Xcode swift links and Android Gradle tasks.
9.  **Chrome Extension Development:** Follow strict Manifest V3 best practices.
10. **Science Database Queries:** Streamline Clinical, Genomic, and Chemical API mappings.

---

## ⚡ BỘ 33 PHÍM TẮT SLASH COMMANDS (33 SLASH COMMANDS SHIMS)

Cline must intercept the following commands and execute them using the dedicated multi-agent workflows:

1.  **`/plan`** — Formulate a detailed phase plan, identify file boundaries, and wait for Approve.
2.  **`/tdd`** — Write a failing test case, build the green code, and refactor.
3.  **`/build-fix`** — Run compiler typecheck, isolate exact lines, and fix with surgical diffs.
4.  **`/code-review`** — Conduct senior code reviews on unstaged git diffs with strict noise filters.
5.  **`/security-scan`** — Run OWASP audits and sweeps for secrets and credentials.
6.  **`/update-docs`** — Crawl codebase with AST and update codemaps in `docs/CODEMAPS/`.
7.  **`/refactor-clean`** — Trigger knip/depcheck to remove dead code and clean unused files.
8.  **`/checkpoint`** — Wrap stage commits into clean, descriptive git commit logs.
9.  **`/cost-report`** — Read `agent_memory.md` to report context tokens and API expenditures.
10. **`/sessions`** — View active agent workspace states under `scratch/`.
11. **`/db-migrate`** — Validate PostgreSQL migrations and test schema constraints.
12. **`/perf-audit`** — Analyze memory usage and flag O(n) runtime complexity.
13. **`/a11y-check`** — Audit HTML markup and styling for WCAG 2.2 accessibility compliance.
14. **`/seo-optimize`** — Auto-inject metadata descriptions, page titles, and canonical headers.
15. **`/secrets-sweep`** — Intercept and remove hardcoded API Keys, SSH keys, or JWT tokens.
16. **`/api-mock`** — Generate Express/FastAPI mock server files for offline integration testing.
17. **`/test-e2e`** — Execute Playwright browser automation tests for key user journeys.
18. **`/memory-leak`** — Run heap snapshot diagnostics to hunt down memory leaks.
19. **`/package-dist`** — Prepare and compile distribution assets into clean production bundles.
20. **`/sanitise-fork`** — Scrape internal assets, clean git branches, prepare for open-sourcing.
21. **`/science-query`** — Retrieve database information from NCBI, PubChem, and ChEMBL.
22. **`/firebase-rules`** — Audit Firestore/Storage security rules for public write leaks.
23. **`/android-build`** — Orchestrate Android compilation, emulator setup, and APK assembly.
24. **`/ios-setup`** — Link Swift packages and resolve CocoaPods/SPM conflicts.
25. **`/lcp-optimize`** — Solve Core Web Vitals issues, lazy-load media, and set priority fetch.
26. **`/chrome-ext`** — Troubleshoot Chrome Manifest V3 side panels, workers, and content scripts.
27. **`/help`** — Show the complete command list and explanation of expert agents.
28. **`/agent-register`** — Fetch registry status of the 60 subagents.
29. **`/prompt-gen`** — Generate system prompt overrides for local ChatML LLMs.
30. **`/loop-telemetry`** — Run compile loops checks and count failure retries.
31. **`/rollback`** — Safely discard changes and return files to last verified commit.
32. **`/diagnose`** — Verify local workspace configurations, `.gitignore`, and env flags.
33. **`/publish`** — Push complete validated work to GitHub with formatted tag notes.
